<?xml version="1.0" ?>
<!--
This is an example for a directory.xml.
This 4 tags are all you can use in this file.
No of the tags is needed for the lX Content
to work correct.
If you don't give a tag, the value will be
generated automatically.

category_name contains the name of the category,
which is added to menu.
default: the name of the category-directory

menu contains item-tags.
A item-tag can eather contains a file-tag, which
contains the filename of the file the menuitem
should point to, or contains a raw_data-tag.
Raw data is added to the menu how it is.
default: all *.html-files will be added to menu

You can use stylesheet-tag to specify a stylesheet
which should be use for the category.
If there is no "%stylesheet%" in the templatefile
this tag wouldn't be used.
default: the stylesheet specified in config.php

main_page is the filename of the page, which should
be loaded, when the category is chosen in mainmenu
default: the alphabetically first *.html file in
the directoy

category_name and main_page should be defined ;)
-->
<directory>
	<category_name>Test Category</category_name>
<!--
	<menu>
		<item>
			<file>faq_hacken.html</file>
		</item>
		<item>
			<raw_data><a href="http://example.com">example.com</a></raw_data>
		</item>
	</menu>
	<stylesheet>irgendwas anderes</stylesheet>
-->
	<main_page>testpage.html</main_page>
</directory>
